title: The surprising reason it’s so hard to meet women at clubs. #datingcoach
caption: false

channel_info.title: Robbie Kramer
channel_info.description:
I'm Robbie Kramer 🎙Host of The Inner Confidence Podcast & Founder of Inner Confidence, Inc.

I lived an exhilarating single life filled with adventures and lessons, and ultimately achieved what I had always aspired to – finding an amazing, feminine, and loving wife. 

I believe my experiences provide a rare balance of wild freedom and committed love, equipping me with the insights to help you navigate the complexities of dating and relationships in today's world. Let me guide you to embrace your desires, improve your social prowess, and ultimately attract the partner who aligns with your highest aspirations.

You won’t find any fluffy, new-age, or cringy stuff here, just tested, proven and actionable advice that yields results.

Apply to join our exclusive Inner Confidence Community of ambitious men who are actively working together to achieve their goals faster   ► https://innerconfidence.com/community

You can email me at robbie@innerconfidence.com with any questions or comments.

transcription: {"text": "The whole business model of a promoter, it's a very lifestyle-driven business. They never actually make money, but they have fun. They have the access of a billionaire, but they're broke. The way that model houses work is promoters need to bring girls to nightclubs, right? Like that's how they get paid. They have $50, $100 per head. But getting the girls to actually show up is like herding cats. And the club would give them a table, a very good real estate, like next to the DJ booth or right when you enter. That's why whenever you walk into like a club, LA or Vegas, like the first table you see, it's always a promoter table. And you're like, oh, there's so many chicks here. But it's like, you have no access to those girls. It's like, they're there with the promoter. You can't get at that table. It just looks good, right? So you're like the typical dude walks in like, this place is awesome. Let me buy a bottle. Let me spend all my money. It's like, it's bullshit. It's all smoke and mirrors, right?
